<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15033c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15033c">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15033c"> 33(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Hungrvaka</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Of &Iacute;sleif and Gizur there are also accounts in the book called <i><mark>Hungrvaka</mark></i>, written about or soon after 1200, and so named by its author because he hoped that it might &lsquo;wake hunger&rsquo; in its readers to know more about the great and pious men whose careers he relates. <small> W. A. Craige, <a name="ICEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ICEL"><cite title="source">The Icelandic Sagas</cite></a>, (1913) 71</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15209c" href="c15all.htm#c15209c">VI.C.15:209(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
